The phone itself (IPhone XS) is 5 stars

The 'refurb' aspect is 4 stars this time around since there was no plastic protection on the screen on this one
The first one I bought (Note 9) had this, so I would have expected Amazon (or their 3rd party refurb partner) to provide this every time, I guess not
That said, there was one small <1mm scuff on the middle-left of the screen, which could have occurred prior to being refurb'd or during shipping I suppose
Either way, it did come with a tempered glass screen protector which was a plus, and I can't see the scuff at all with the screen protector on the phone
Overall satisfied and would buy again - but I think Amazon/3rd party refurb partner have some inconsistencies to address in their refurb process

Logic Board Failed After 18 Months
After an extremely frustrating experience in with Apple Support during the COVID crisis
I was told that the Power Up issue with my iPhone XS was a failed Logic Board (this took 7 days, several calls, chats)
This phone was 18 months old and had no problems leading up to the failure
I did not get the Logic Board failure explanation until I spoke/chatted with not less than 5 Apple Support people in at least 3 countries
I finally got a nice duo based in OK would were honest and frankly not rude (weird for Apple which in the past has always had polite Support people)

While failed Logic board was the diagnosis, the way this was handled and the fact that Apple has stopped selling iPhone XS makes me believe that the Phone had bad Logic Boards from the beginning and Apple made a financial and marketing decision not to make this public and simply discontinue sales of the Phone rather than make it part of the Exchange and Repair Extension Programs
Since Apple has stopped selling the Phone XS, I feel obligated to let people know that I believe that the Logic Boards were faulty from the beginning and Apple's quality control may be failing
I elected not to purchase the replacement and I will use my old 7 until I have confidence that Apple is not selling inferior tech
